You need to put `System.out.println(i);` before `continue` statement. 

    for (int i = 0; i &lt; 10; i++) {
        System.out.println(i);
        continue;
    }

Continue tells `for` loop to keep on and breaks the current iteration, so in your version `System.out.println(i)` is not reachable.

***Option***: You can omit `continue` as it is redundant being last statement in the loop (@Pshemo)

